<Window x:Class="Circles.HelpWindow"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:Circles"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="Help" Width="850" WindowStartupLocation="CenterScreen" MinWidth="640" MinHeight="480">
    <Grid Background="#FFF0F0F0">
        <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
            <ColumnDefinition Width="13*"/>
            <ColumnDefinition Width="412*"/>
        </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
        <Button x:Name="oKButton" Content="OK" Height="36" VerticalAlignment="Top" HorizontalAlignment="Center" Width="154" Click="oKButton_Click" Margin="0,872,0,0" Grid.Column="1"/>
        <ScrollViewer Margin="0,0,0,101" VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto" HorizontalContentAlignment="Stretch" HorizontalScrollBarVisibility="Auto" Padding="14" Grid.ColumnSpan="2">
            <TextBlock x:Name="textBlock" TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="16" Foreground="Black" ScrollViewer.VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto" Height="845" Width="748"><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="The goal of this game is to maximize the number of points."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="The player earns points by successively moving balls of the same color into certain groups."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="When a group is formed, the group's balls disappear and points are added."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="-------------------------------------------------- ---------------------------------"/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="This game features a board that consists of squares."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="The board has a certain number of rows and a certain number of columns."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="Arrays are specific intersections of a row and a column."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="Balls may be placed in fields."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="-------------------------------------------------- ---------------------------------"/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="There are different types of balls."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="Colored balls have one of 16 colors and can double the number of points."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="In addition, there are rainbow balls that work like a joker in some card games, so they fulfill the function of being any color, the color that is needed, but in appearance they always have the texture of a rainbow."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="-------------------------------------------------- ---------------------------------"/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="The gameplay is as follows:"/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text=" - At the beginning of the game, a certain number of randomly selected balls will appear on randomly selected fields, which must be empty beforehand."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text=" - Next, the following loop is repeated:"/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="Waiting for the player to activate the field the ball is in. Then it waits for the player to activate an empty field, that is, the field where he wants to move the ball."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="If there is a path of empty squares between the square containing the ball the player wants to move and the empty square the player wants to move the ball to, then the ball is moved."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="If certain groups of balls have been created, the balls of that group will disappear and points will be added and this loop will start again from the beginning, if a group of balls of a certain shape has not been created, a certain number of random balls will appear in random fields and only then the loop will start again from the beginning."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas"/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="The game is played until all fields are filled with balls."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="-------------------------------------------------- ---------------------------------"/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="Many variable properties of this game can be set through the form, which, among other options, also appears after pressing the F6 key."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="-------------------------------------------------- ---------------------------------"/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="Variable properties have the following default values:"/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="The dimensions of the board are 9 by 9."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="The colors used are: light green, red, dark blue, yellow, light blue, purple and brown. "/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="5 balls appear at the beginning of the game and 3 balls appear during the game."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="The balls are folded into the shape of a line, either horizontally, vertically or diagonally from the left or right."/><LineBreak/><Run FontFamily="Consolas" Text="The minimum length of this line must be 5 balls."/></TextBlock>
        </ScrollViewer>


    </Grid>
</Window>
